Econometrics of Network Data // Simulating and estimating peer
effect models and network formation models. The class of peer
effect models includes linear-in-means models (Lee, 2004;
doi:10.1111/j.1468-0262.2004.00558.x), Tobit models (Xu and
Lee, 2015; doi:10.1016/j.jeconom.2015.05.004), and discrete
numerical data models (Houndetoungan, 2024;
doi:10.2139/ssrn.3721250). The network formation models include
pair-wise regressions with degree heterogeneity (Graham, 2017;
doi:10.3982/ECTA12679) and exponential random graph models
(Mele, 2017; doi:10.3982/ECTA10400).
